The `sorry` is at the end of the proof of `helper`.
The goal is `⊢ AEStronglyMeasurable (enorm ∘ T' g₁) (ν.restrict G)`.

Looking at the context, we have `g₁ : α → NNReal` which is `measurable` (as per the definition `g₁ := fun x ↦ Real.toNNReal (RCLike.re (g x))` and `g` being `stronglyMeasurable`).
`T'` is `HasRestrictedWeakType T' p p' μ ν c`.
`T'` maps `a.e.m.` functions to `a.e.m.` functions (from `T'_subadd`, `T'_submul`).
`T'` maps `measurable` functions to `a.e.m.` functions (specifically, `g₁` is `measurable`).
`T' g₁` is `a.e.m.` with respect to `μ`.
`enorm` is `continuous`.
The composition of `continuous` functions is `continuous`.
`enorm ∘ T' g₁` is `continuous`.
`continuous` implies `a.e.m.` (almost everywhere measurable).
So `enorm ∘ T' g₁` is `a.e.m.` with respect to `ν`.

We need to show `AEStronglyMeasurable (enorm ∘ T' g₁) (ν.restrict G)`.
This is equivalent to showing that `f = (enorm ∘ T' g₁)` is `a.e.m.` and `Continuous` at points in the interior of the set.

